Perfect! I now have all the information needed. Let me create a comprehensive report for you:

## Complete Registry Structure Report for shadcn/ui Stepper Component

Based on my exploration of the shadcn/ui codebase, here's the complete registry structure and how to add a new "Stepper" component:

---

### **File Structure Overview**

The registry system has the following hierarchy:

```
apps/v4/registry/
├── new-york-v4/
│   ├── registry.ts           (Main entry point - combines all sub-registries)
│   ├── ui/_registry.ts       (UI components)
│   ├── examples/_registry.ts (Example implementations)
│   ├── blocks/_registry.ts   (Complex layout blocks)
│   ├── hooks/_registry.ts    (Custom hooks)
│   ├── lib/_registry.ts      (Utilities)
│   ├── internal/_registry.ts (Internal/sidebar components)
│   └── charts/_registry.ts   (Chart blocks)
├── config.ts                 (Configuration and schema)
├── themes.ts                 (Theme definitions)
└── [other directories]
```

---

### **1. UI Component Registry Format**
**File:** `/apps/v4/registry/new-york-v4/ui/_registry.ts`

**Complete Structure (Lines 1-705):**

A UI component entry has this format:

```typescript
import { type Registry } from "shadcn/schema"

export const ui: Registry["items"] = [
  {
    name: "stepper",              // unique identifier
